#REDIRECT [[Critical Depth]]
{{dicdef}}

'''Critical depth''' is the depth in any [[waterbody]] (ocean, sea or lake) at which the rate of [[photosynthesis]] equals the rate of respiration of a primary producer (mainly [[phytoplankton]]).

