'''Grzegorz Piramowicz''' (25 November 1735 in [[Lwów]] – 14 November 1801 in [[Międzyrzec Podlaski]]) was a Polish Catholic priest, educator, writer, and philosopher. He was a member of the [[Commission of National Education]] and [[Society for Elementary Books]], and one of the founders of the [[Society of Friends of the Constitution]].

